COMMITTEE ON BUDGET, APPROPRIATIONS AND FINANCE
BILL NO. 36-0018
Thirty-Sixth Legislature of the Virgin Islands
February 27, 2025
An Act amending title 3 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 25, subchapter V, section 551 by
increasing the minimum salary amount for teachers from $3,200 per annum to $60,000 per
annum and by making technical amendments
PROPOSED BY: Senators Kurt A. Vialet and Marvin A. Blyden
1 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the Virgin Islands:
2 SECTION 1. Title 3 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 25, subchapter V is amended as
3 follows:
4 (a) In the second occurrence of section 551, strike the title “Purpose and Coverage”
5 and insert “Pay Plan”;
6 (b) In the second occurrence of section 551, Schedule III, paragraph (1), strike
7 “$3,200” and insert “$60,000”; and
8 (c) Re-designate the second occurrence of section 551 as section 551e.
9 SECTION 2. Section 1 takes effect at the beginning of the 2025/2026 school year.
10 BILL SUMMARY
11 The bill amends title 3 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 25, subchapter V, section 551 by
12 increasing the minimum salary amount for a teacher from $3,200 per annum to $60,000 per

